## 7. Personalized Recommendations for a Specific User

**"Based on similar users, what should we recommend to user 101?"**

```sql
WITH user_products AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT user_id, product_id FROM orders
),
-- Step 1: Find top 10 most similar users to 101
similar_users AS (
  SELECT
    b.user_id  AS similar_user,
    COUNT(*)   AS common_products       -- proxy for similarity
  FROM user_products a
  JOIN user_products b
    ON  a.product_id = b.product_id
    AND b.user_id   != 101
  WHERE a.user_id = 101
  GROUP BY b.user_id
  ORDER BY common_products DESC
  LIMIT 10
),
-- Step 2: Products user 101 already bought
already_bought AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT product_id FROM orders WHERE user_id = 101
),
-- Step 3: Aggregate products from similar users, score by weighted support
candidates AS (
  SELECT
    up.product_id,
    SUM(su.common_products)          AS recommendation_score,  -- weighted by similarity
    COUNT(DISTINCT su.similar_user)  AS supporting_users        -- how many similar users have it
  FROM similar_users su
  JOIN user_products up ON su.similar_user = up.user_id
  WHERE up.product_id NOT IN (SELECT product_id FROM already_bought)
  GROUP BY up.product_id
)
SELECT
  c.product_id,
  p.name,
  p.category,
  c.recommendation_score,
  c.supporting_users
FROM candidates c
JOIN products p ON c.product_id = p.product_id
ORDER BY recommendation_score DESC
LIMIT 20;
```

### CTE-Level I/O Trace

User 101 has bought: {P1, P2, P3}

**`similar_users`:**
```
similar_user | common_products
U5           | 3   (bought P1, P2, P3)
U7           | 2   (bought P1, P2)
U9           | 1   (bought P3)
```

**Products from similar users NOT in {P1, P2, P3}:**
```
similar_user | product_id | common_products
U5           | P10        | 3
U5           | P11        | 3
U7           | P10        | 2
U9           | P15        | 1
```

**`candidates` — GROUP BY product_id, SUM(common_products):**
```
product_id | recommendation_score | supporting_users
P10        | 3+2=5                | 2
P11        | 3                    | 1
P15        | 1                    | 1
```

**Output:**
```
product_id | name | category | recommendation_score | supporting_users
P10        | ...  | ...      | 5                    | 2
P11        | ...  | ...      | 3                    | 1
P15        | ...  | ...      | 1                    | 1
```

**Why `SUM(common_products)` as score?** A recommendation supported by a user with 3 products in common with 101 is stronger evidence than one supported by a user with 1 product in common. This weights each similar user's contribution by their similarity to 101.

