## 8. Item-Item Recs for a Specific User ("Because You Bought X")

**"For user 101 who bought {P1, P2, P3}, find all items co-purchased with those items, excluding already-bought items."**

This is the scalable FAANG pattern — pre-computed item similarities, applied per user at query time.

```sql
WITH already_bought AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT product_id FROM orders WHERE user_id = 101
),
-- Step 1: For each product 101 bought, find co-purchased items
co_purchases AS (
  SELECT
    a.product_id  AS seed_product,     -- what user already bought
    b.product_id  AS recommended,      -- what to recommend
    COUNT(DISTINCT a.order_id) AS co_count
  FROM orders a
  JOIN orders b
    ON  a.order_id   = b.order_id
    AND a.product_id != b.product_id   -- not the same product
  WHERE a.product_id IN (SELECT product_id FROM already_bought)
    AND b.product_id NOT IN (SELECT product_id FROM already_bought)
  GROUP BY a.product_id, b.product_id
),
-- Step 2: Aggregate across all seed products
aggregated AS (
  SELECT
    recommended,
    SUM(co_count)                 AS total_co_purchase_score,
    COUNT(DISTINCT seed_product)  AS triggered_by_n_seeds,   -- diversity signal
    MAX(co_count)                 AS best_single_seed_score
  FROM co_purchases
  GROUP BY recommended
)
SELECT
  a.recommended                    AS product_id,
  p.name,
  p.category,
  a.total_co_purchase_score,
  a.triggered_by_n_seeds,
  a.best_single_seed_score
FROM aggregated a
JOIN products p ON a.recommended = p.product_id
ORDER BY total_co_purchase_score DESC
LIMIT 20;
```

### CTE-Level I/O Trace

User 101 has bought: {P1, P2}

**Self-join on orders, seed in {P1,P2}, recommended NOT in {P1,P2}:**

```
seed_product | recommended | co_count
P1           | P4          | 15   (P4 bought with P1 in 15 orders)
P1           | P5          | 8
P2           | P4          | 12
P2           | P6          | 5
```

**`aggregated`:**
```
recommended | total_score | triggered_by | best_single
P4          | 15+12=27    | 2            | 15
P5          | 8           | 1            | 8
P6          | 5           | 1            | 5
```

**Key insight — `triggered_by_n_seeds`:** P4 is recommended by BOTH P1 AND P2 the user bought. This "triangulation" signal is much stronger than if only one seed triggered it. You can use this as a secondary sort or boost multiplier.

