## 11. Session-Based Recommendations (Co-Views × CVR)

**"Right now in this session, user viewed P1 → show products often viewed alongside P1 that convert well."**

This powers real-time "also viewed" rails without requiring login history.

```sql
-- Step 1: Deduplicate views per session (one row per session-product pair)
WITH session_views AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT session_id, product_id
  FROM sessions
  WHERE event_type = 'view'
),
-- Step 2: Find products viewed together in same session
co_views AS (
  SELECT
    a.product_id AS product_a,
    b.product_id AS product_b,
    COUNT(DISTINCT a.session_id) AS co_view_sessions
  FROM session_views a
  JOIN session_views b
    ON  a.session_id = b.session_id   -- same session
    AND a.product_id < b.product_id
  GROUP BY a.product_id, b.product_id
),
-- Step 3: Conversion rate per product (sessions that purchased / sessions that viewed)
conversion AS (
  SELECT
    product_id,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_type = 'view'     THEN session_id END) AS view_sessions,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_type = 'purchase' THEN session_id END) AS purchase_sessions,
    ROUND(
      COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_type = 'purchase' THEN session_id END) * 100.0 /
      NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN event_type = 'view' THEN session_id END), 0)
    , 2) AS conversion_rate
  FROM sessions
  GROUP BY product_id
)
-- Step 4: Score = co-view frequency × target product's conversion rate
SELECT
  cv.product_a,
  cv.product_b,
  cv.co_view_sessions,
  c.conversion_rate AS product_b_cvr,
  -- Co-viewed often AND converts well = best recommendation
  ROUND(cv.co_view_sessions * c.conversion_rate / 100.0, 4) AS recommendation_score
FROM co_views cv
JOIN conversion c ON cv.product_b = c.product_id
ORDER BY recommendation_score DESC;
```

### CTE-Level I/O Trace

**Input `sessions`:**
```
session_id | product_id | event_type
S1         | P1         | view
S1         | P2         | view
S1         | P2         | purchase
S2         | P1         | view
S2         | P3         | view
S3         | P2         | view
S3         | P2         | purchase
```

**`session_views`** (DISTINCT):
```
session_id | product_id
S1         | P1
S1         | P2
S2         | P1
S2         | P3
S3         | P2
```

**`co_views`** — same session, product_a < product_b:
```
S1: (P1, P2)
S2: (P1, P3)
→
product_a | product_b | co_view_sessions
P1        | P2        | 1
P1        | P3        | 1
```

**`conversion`:**
```
product_id | view_sessions | purchase_sessions | cvr
P1         | 2             | 0                 | 0.00%
P2         | 2             | 2                 | 100.00%
P3         | 1             | 0                 | 0.00%
```

**Final scores:**
```
product_a | product_b | co_views | b_cvr  | rec_score
P1        | P2        | 1        | 100.00 | 1.0000   ← surface P2 when user views P1
P1        | P3        | 1        | 0.00   | 0.0000   ← P3 never converts, skip
```

**Insight:** P3 is viewed alongside P1 as often as P2, but P3 never converts. The score correctly surfaces P2. Pure co-view frequency would mistakenly treat them equally.

