## 16. Key Takeaways Cheatsheet

### Metric Formula Reference

| Metric | Formula | Use When |
|--------|---------|----------|
| **Jaccard** | `co_count / (count_a + count_b - co_count)` | Binary data, normalizes for popularity |
| **Lift** | `(co_count × total) / (count_a × count_b)` | Measure co-occurrence beyond chance |
| **Confidence A→B** | `co_count / count_a` | Directional rule strength |
| **Cosine** | `dot_product / (norm_a × norm_b)` | Weighted/implicit feedback |
| **Category affinity** | `COUNT in category / total COUNT` (window fn) | Personalize by taste profile |
| **Trending score** | `p_7d × 0.5 + p_30d × 0.3 + unique_buyers × 0.2` | Cold start / new users |
| **Engagement rate** | `unique engagers / unique viewers` | Content creator health |

### Pattern → SQL Technique Map

| Problem | Core SQL Pattern | Key Trick |
|---------|-----------------|-----------|
| Co-purchased pairs | Self-join on `order_id` | `product_a < product_b` to avoid duplicates |
| User similarity (binary) | Self-join on `product_id` | `user_a < user_b` + Jaccard normalization |
| User similarity (weighted) | Self-join on `product_id` | `SUM(a.score × b.score)` for dot product |
| Top-N per user | Window function | `RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY user ORDER BY score DESC)` |
| Category affinity | Window function | `COUNT(*) / SUM(COUNT(*)) OVER (PARTITION BY user_id)` |
| Best post per month | ROW_NUMBER | `PARTITION BY author_id, month ORDER BY er DESC` |
| Diversity constraint | ROW_NUMBER | `PARTITION BY user_id, category ORDER BY score DESC` |
| Popularity fallback | CASE WHEN + date arithmetic | Weight recency buckets |
| MoM trend | LAG | `LAG(metric) OVER (PARTITION BY entity ORDER BY period)` |
| Item-item + fallback merge | FULL OUTER JOIN + COALESCE | `COALESCE(item_item_score, pop_score)` |
| Session-based | Co-views × CVR | Self-join `sessions` on `session_id` |

### Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Duplicate pairs (A,B) and (B,A) | `AND product_a < product_b` in every pair-join |
| Division by zero in similarity | `NULLIF(denominator, 0)` |
| Recommending already-bought items | `NOT IN (SELECT product_id FROM already_bought)` |
| `NOT IN` with NULLs (returns no rows) | Use `NOT EXISTS` instead |
| Counting events not users | `COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)`, never `COUNT(*)` in funnels |
| All recs from same category | `ROW_NUMBER() PARTITION BY user_id, category <= N` |
| Lift = 1 meaning "good" | Lift = 1 means independence; you want Lift >> 1 |
| Popular items dominating Jaccard | Jaccard handles this; Lift/Confidence do not |
| User-user at scale | Pre-compute item-item offline; apply per user at query time |

### The Production Decision Tree

```
Has user purchase/event history?
├── YES: Item-item collaborative filtering (primary)
│         + category affinity boost
│         + diversity constraint (max N per category)
│         + fallback slots filled from trending
└── NO (new user): Popularity / Trending fallback
                    + (if we know category from signup) category top items
                    → Transition to collaborative as history accumulates
```

